# ── Engine internals ──────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# ── Workspace (B) artifacts that may surface here during dev/test ─
# .state/ holds runtime bookkeeping (cycle counter, tick.log, locks,
# sha256 caches). It legitimately exists only inside ${WORK_DIR}, but
# git-ignore at A's root is a safety net in case of stray test runs.
.state/

# ── Stale artifact from old generate_context.py ───────────────────
# The old version of scripts/generate_context.py wrote a copy of
# .cursorrules back into A as `workspace.cursorrules`. The new version
# only writes into B/.cursorrules. Ignored to keep the artifact from
# coming back if anyone reverts the script.
workspace.cursorrules

# ── Demo training artifacts (regenerable) ─────────────────────────
# demo/ ships sample data + scripts so users can run a no-GPU demo,
# but the actual training output (logs, checkpoints) is regenerated
# every run; don't commit it.
demo/results/
demo/__pycache__/
